	   <tr><td colspan=2>A few notes. <br><br>1. Most if not all haste songs are based on singing so an instument will not help you. <br><br>2. You can twist and do damage.<br><br>3. Clarity song is singing. <br><br>Lets take a short example.<br><br>You want to do haste,healing and chain to keep mob fleeing.<br><br>Chain is singing.no effect gained with instrument<br>Haste is singing.no effect gained with instrument<br>Hymn is stringed. 100% gain with instrument.<br><br>You are in a group with one or two tanks who take damage (if you got a healer you will play mana song instead of hyrm when ur not fighting) <br><br>So if you dual wield and hit for around 20 for each weapon (not included procs) and lets say you hit 1/2 of the times thats about 100 dam in 6 seconds <br><br>But if you choose to use a lute instead of meleeing you could have healed the tank 6 points more or so by using an instrument not doing anything.<br><br>So what would you rather have. 6 hps more on tanks or 100 dam to a mob in 6 secs. I know what i prefer <br>&nbsp;<br>Cyrix<br>60 Bard<br>Test</td></tr>
